    "Criteria for Model FixationThis section, discusses about the criteria used in many papers to fix the model, the reasons behind the high accuracy achieved, the unique field in which the models are used, and the domains in which they have been used the most.The performance of the models is evaluated using Top1 accuracy and it measures the percentage of images for which the predicted class is the same as the ground class.",
    "However, some papers also use top-5 accuracy, which measures the percentage of images for which the predicted class is among the top-5 predicted classes [19].",
